<section>
    <h2>Overview</h2>
    <p>The <code>&lt;content-swap&gt;</code> component toggles between two content faces with configurable transition effects. It manages <code>inert</code> on the hidden face so screen readers only announce visible content.</p>
    <p>The transition type is a styling concern (<code>data-transition</code>), while duration and easing come from VB motion tokens &mdash; so themes automatically control the personality of every swap.</p>

    <browser-window
      src="/docs/examples/demos/content-swap-basic.html"
      url="https://vanilla-breeze.dev/content-swap"
      title="Content Swap Demo"
      shadow>
    </browser-window>

    <code-block language="html" show-lines label="Basic content swap (flip)">{{ basicFlipCode | escape }}</code-block>

    <aside class="note">
      <strong>Why a web component?</strong> CSS <code>backface-visibility: hidden</code> is visual only &mdash; screen readers still read the hidden face. JavaScript is required to toggle <code>inert</code> on the hidden face.
    </aside>
  </section>

